Biweekly personalization review.

Read ${BORG_ROOT}/mrs-beast/CLAUDE.md and ${BORG_ROOT}/mrs-beast/USER.md. Review the last ~2 weeks of session history in ~/.claude/projects/ — find the subdirectory whose name corresponds to your current working directory (Claude Code derives the dir name from the workspace path).

Ask: do these files still accurately reflect how I'm being used as the social-media-mgr and who John is as my user? Has my role or understanding of John shifted? Are there new responsibilities, preferences, or things to drop?

If changes are warranted, propose specific edits and send them to John by piping the message into `${BORG_ROOT}/.bin/notify-telegram.sh mrs-beast` (reads the message from stdin, delivers to John's Telegram). Otherwise send a one-line confirmation the same way.
